oliferation of nuclear weapons in longstanding regional conflicts. Optimism that small and medium nuclear powers can easily achieve "stable" nuclear balances is, he believes, unwarranted.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aInternational Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  aInternational Relations.  aNuclear Risks.  aPolitical Science.  aSecurity Affairs .  aSecurity studies .  aStudies in Security Affairs.  aThe Sources of Military Doctrine.  aarms control .  adynamics of escalation.  aglobal nuclear warfare .  aintensification of conflict.  ainternational security .  ainternational security issues .  alimited war .  amilitary escalation .  amilitary policy .  amilitary science .  amilitary strategy .  amilitary studies .  amutually assured destruction .  anuclear Armageddon .  anuclear defenses .  anuclear military war .  anuclear politics .  anuclear revolution .  anuclear risks .  anuclear strategy .  anuclear studies .  anuclear threshold .  anuclear war .  anuclear war potential .  anuclear war strategy .  anuclear warfare .  anuclear warfare history .  anuclear weaponry.  anuclear weapons .  anuclear weapons proliferation.  asecurity issues .  awar endgame .  awar strategy .  awar theory .08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080146838440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801468384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801468384/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package